JOHANNESBURG - Lethebo Rabalao, popularly known as the Doom Pastor, has been found guilty on four charges of assault. Rabalao used an insecticide on congregants, claiming that he was instructed by God to heal them. READ: Snake pastor at it again with cockroaches and 'poisonous' flowers The controversial Limpopo pastor has also been found guilty on three charges of contravening the Agricultural Act by spraying an insecticide on people. He made headlines in 2016 when videos of him surfaced, leading the health department in the province to lay charges against him. eNCA